                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="116575" author="adilger" created="Wed, 27 May 2015 18:18:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Haven&apos;t seen this in a long time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41464" author="yujian" created="Thu, 5 Jul 2012 00:34:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Lai,&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for the explanation. Next time I perform 1.8-&amp;gt;2.x upgrading testing, I&apos;ll regenerate config logs to run sanity test 120*. For the testing without regenerating config logs, I&apos;ll skip sanity test 120*.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41463" author="laisiyao" created="Wed, 4 Jul 2012 23:53:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Yujian, the main cause is that 2.x config contains section for lmv, but 1.8 not. And some ELC logic is implemented in lmv layer. A simple way to fix it is to regenerate config logs, please refer to &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.lustre.org/manual/LustreManual18_HTML/ConfiguringLustre.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.lustre.org/manual/LustreManual18_HTML/ConfiguringLustre.html&lt;/a&gt; 4.3.11.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this works, do you think it&apos;s acceptable. IIRC, regenerating config logs is a common way to fix config issues in upgrade, is it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40189" author="yujian" created="Thu, 7 Jun 2012 10:13:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same issue occurred while running sanity tests after clean upgrading from Lustre 1.8.8-wc1 to 2.1.2:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;client-1: == sanity test 120a: Early Lock Cancel: mkdir test == 04:40:35 (1339069235)
client-1: ldlm.namespaces.lustre-MDT0000-mdc-ffff8802a90f9800.lru_size=400
client-1: ldlm.namespaces.lustre-OST0000-osc-ffff8802a90f9800.lru_size=400
client-1: ldlm.namespaces.lustre-OST0001-osc-ffff8802a90f9800.lru_size=400
client-1:  sanity test_120a: @@@@@@ FAIL: 1 blocking RPC occured.
client-1: Dumping lctl log to /home/yujian/test_logs/2012-06-07/043300/sanity.test_120a.*.1339069236.log
client-1: FAIL 120a (3s)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maloo report: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c250c2d6-b0d3-11e1-99ce-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c250c2d6-b0d3-11e1-99ce-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="29798" author="yujian" created="Fri, 24 Feb 2012 07:15:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same issue occurred while running sanity tests after clean upgrading from Lustre 1.8.7-wc1 to 2.1.1:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/3d45f592-5ee0-11e1-ab6b-5254004bbbd3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/3d45f592-5ee0-11e1-ab6b-5254004bbbd3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20994" author="laisiyao" created="Sun, 9 Oct 2011 22:22:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;review is on &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1339&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,1339&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19956" author="yujian" created="Mon, 5 Sep 2011 07:39:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The same issue occurred while running sanity tests after clean upgrading from Lustre 1.8.5/1.8.6-wc1 to 2.1.0:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/17b5046c-d7b3-11e0-8d02-52540025f9af&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/17b5046c-d7b3-11e0-8d02-52540025f9af&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19784" author="laisiyao" created="Wed, 31 Aug 2011 04:23:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The cause is because ELC (early lock cancel) flags is set in LMV layer, but for 1.8 &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; 2.1 case, LMV doesn&apos;t exist. I will move ELC flags setting into llite for 2.1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19270" author="yujian" created="Tue, 16 Aug 2011 05:31:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lai Siyao would work on this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
